post_text:
We miss you and are so excited to welcome you back to school this fall! We are planning for a school year of learning together in an in-person classroom environment. However, we realize things can change between now and the first day of school. Take a moment to watch this video to hear more about how we’re preparing for the 2020-21 school year. We created detailed plans around four learning scenarios. These plans are in-line with our state's department of education plan, which outlines required and recommended safety protocols for the 2020-21 school year based on the status of coronavirus in our community.
For the most up to date information on back to school plan, please visit: https://www.nhaschools.com/en/COVID-19

post_text: It is our pleasure to announce that Keystone had a winner and a finalist in NHA’s Moral Focus Writing and Art contest. Congratulations to Rami Fadel for 5th place in the K-2 Writing Division, and Anaya Smith for qualifying as a finalist in the 6-8 Art Division. NHA had 363 entries submitted from 46 schools this year. We are proud of all the Keystone students who submitted artwork and/or writing pieces. The depth of understanding of the Moral Focus virtues that was demonstrated through their work is incredible and reflects the hard work and commitment to Moral Focus. Way to go Keystone and keep shining!

post_text: Mrs. Quinn, our 8th grade ELA teacher, has started a middle school book club for all 6th-8th grade students. The students and staff vote on a book and have a month to read it. The only requirement is that students must purchase their own book and read it before the meeting. The book club just finished their first book last Thursday and voted on reading Pax by Sarah Pennypacker for March! The next meeting date will be Thursday, March 26 during middle school lunch and recess. This is a great opportunity for students to interact with staff and bond over their enthusiasm and passion for reading. The book club is always interested in more people to join!

post_text:
Did you know that Miss Karpinski started a free after school art club?



Keystone Academy’s Art Club is compiled of 5th-8th grade students who work in all types of mediums with a variety of ideas. There isn’t a limit of the number of members and it’s free to join! The only requirement is an interest in making something you are proud of as well as a willingness to take artistic risks. So far this school year, student have created collaborative art modeled after the Sumi Ink Club, experimented with mixed media paintings, crafted 3D sculptures larger than life and started a personal art series that can continue even once the meetings are finished. Our Wednesday afternoons in the art room have created a community that values individuality and supports one another. Being able to come together each week and see what others are working on can spark new ideas and lead to long-term friendships with peers. We look forward to seeing how we can collaborate to continue doing good for others through our art each week.

I hope everyone is enjoying their summer!! It's been a HOT one!
Please remember to login to your parent portal at www.keystoneacademy.org and fill out your annual enrollment forms. We don't have many of them done and it is the third week of July already! These are your forms that need to be completed prior to the first day of school. We must have 100% of these completed. Please let us know if you are having difficulty completing the forms as we have hard copies available in the school office if you need to pick them up to complete them. Thank you so much for your continued support and cooperation☺️
